%[text] $\\frac{\\;\\;\\;\\;\\ldotp 2667-0\\ldotp 267361}{\\;\\;\\;\\;\\ldotp 2667}\\left(100\\right)\\approx -\\ldotp 24${"editStyle":"visual"} 
%[text] `n=2`
%[text] $\\frac{\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\ldotp 1778-0\\ldotp 178532\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;}{\\ldotp 1778}\\left(100\\right)\\;\\approx -\\ldotp 41${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] `n = 3` 
%[text] $\\frac{\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\ldotp 1185-0\\ldotp 115815\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;}{\\ldotp 1185}\\left(100\\right)\\;\\approx 2\\ldotp 26\\;${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] n=4
%[text] $\\frac{\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\ldotp 079-0\\ldotp 077251\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;}{\\ldotp 079}\\left(100\\right)\\approx 2\\ldotp 21\\;\\;\\;${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] n = 5
%[text] $\\frac{\\ldotp 0527-0\\ldotp 049328}{\\ldotp 0527\\;}\\;\\;\\;\\left(100\\right)\\approx 2\\ldotp 21\\;\\;\\;\\;${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] 
%[text] From just looking at the graph, it appears that P\_0 theoretical looks like it undershot the coding value. This is shown in the percentage of error as a - 2.6. 
