%[text] **L: expected number of customers in the system, being served plus waiting** 
%[text] $L=\\frac{\\;\\frac{\\lambda \\;}{\\mu \\;}}{\\left(1-\\frac{\\;\\lambda \\;}{\\mu {\\;}\_2 }\\right)\\left(1+\\frac{\\;\\lambda \\;}{\\mu {\\;}\_2 }\\right)}=\\frac{\\;\\frac{40\\;}{30\\;}}{\\left(1-\\frac{\\;40\\;}{60}\\right)\\left(1+\\frac{\\;40}{60}\\right)}=\\frac{\\;\\frac{40\\;}{30\\;}}{\\left(\\frac{\\;20\\;}{60}\\right)\\left(\\frac{\\;100}{60}\\right)}\\;\\;\\;=\\frac{\\;\\frac{40\\;}{30\\;}}{\\left(\\frac{\\;2000}{{60}^2 }\\right)}=\\frac{\\;\\frac{40\\;}{30\\;}}{\\left(\\frac{\\;2000}{{60}^2 }\\right)}\\;=\\frac{120\\;}{50}=\\frac{120\\;}{50}=2\\ldotp 4\\;\\;${"editStyle":"visual"}
