%[text] `Mean number in system (L) : 2.411223`
%[text] 
%[text] **L\_q : expected number of customers waiting (not being served)** 
%[text] Little's formula
%[text] $L\_q =\\lambda W\_q \\;${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] $L\_q =40\\;\\left(\\frac{1\\ldotp 6}{60}\\right)=1\\ldotp 0667${"editStyle":"visual"} customers
%[text] $\\frac{\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;1\\ldotp 0667-1\\ldotp 089162\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;}{1\\ldotp 0667}\\left(100\\right)\\approx -2\\ldotp 1${"editStyle":"visual"}
%[text] `Mean number waiting (L_q): 1.089162`
